{"TopicId":3709,"ForumId":25,"TopicTitle":"Single Stage to the Mun!","CreatedByName":"NonWonderDog","CreatedById":10479,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-11T02:11:11Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"NonWonderDog","CreatedById":10479,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-11T02:11:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EGet to the Mun, with one rule: everything that starts on your ship must stay on your ship. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBonus points for orbiting and returning. Massive bonus points for landing. Godlike status for landing, taking off again, and making it back to Kerbin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe bonus challenges will almost certainly require mod parts. Fair parts, even very large ones (KW Challenger, Down Under) are allowed. Or try to do it with Silisko Edition for laughs.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHere\\\u0027s my entry: single stage to Munar orbit with stock parts.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWho here will be the first to land?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"trbinsc","CreatedById":10144,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-11T02:13:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EUsing C7 I went within 1000 meters of the M\u00C3\u00BCn, ran out of rcs fuel, and had to abort the landing. I got back to kerbin alive though. It was only one stage.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"foamyesque","CreatedById":2982,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-11T02:45:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022trbinsc\u0022 data-cite=\u0022trbinsc\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUsing C7 I went within 1000 meters of the M\u00C3\u00BCn, ran out of rcs fuel, and had to abort the landing. I got back to kerbin alive though. It was only one stage.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EC7 is lots of fun, but waaaay overpowered for this kind of challenge. Personally I\\\u0027m boggled by the OP, although I suppose I shouldn\\\u0027t be.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NonWonderDog","CreatedById":10479,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-12T02:45:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ESo it turns out that the hard part of this challenge isn\\\u0027t building the rocket, but flying the monster you have created.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESo far, I haven\\\u0027t been able to control a single stage spacecraft well enough to put it into an efficient pair of transfer orbits to and from the Mun. Landing when main engine gimbaling is your only source of control is its own adventure as well. Putting enough fuel on the ship is by no means the challenge, however.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI\\\u0027m sure one of you is a better pilot than I am!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"foamyesque","CreatedById":2982,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-12T05:58:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI remain boggled, but mostly by how overcomplicated you\\\u0027re making things. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGetting enough juice to land and take off on the Moon is tricky, but doing a TLI, munar orbit, and return to Kerbin can be done with much less than you\\\u0027ve employed.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"geb","CreatedById":5399,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-12T15:42:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://mrp.ath.cx/stuff/ksp_SST%28almost%29M.png\u0022 alt=\u0022ksp_SST%28almost%29M.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUsing Sundaypunch\\\u0027s parts (plus silisko\\\u0027s lunar lander leg), it\\\u0027s really very simple to go to the Mun in a single stage. The tiny liquid fuel engine is \u003Cem\u003Every\u003C/em\u003E efficient and a cluster of seven are powerful enough to do the job.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt doesn\\\u0027t make the return trip though.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"foamyesque","CreatedById":2982,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-12T19:10:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAlrighty, time to back my words up with screenshots!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://awesome.redial.net/SSTM/Pad.png\u0022 alt=\u0022Pad.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://awesome.redial.net/SSTM/TLI%20ready.png\u0022 alt=\u0022TLI ready.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://awesome.redial.net/SSTM/Hohmann%20map.png\u0022 alt=\u0022Hohmann map.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://awesome.redial.net/SSTM/Evasive%20manouvers.png\u0022 alt=\u0022Evasive manouvers.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://awesome.redial.net/SSTM/Orbit%20achieved.png\u0022 alt=\u0022Orbit achieved.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://awesome.redial.net/SSTM/Back%20to%20Kerbin.png\u0022 alt=\u0022Back to Kerbin.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://awesome.redial.net/SSTM/Maximum%20speed.png\u0022 alt=\u0022Maximum speed.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://awesome.redial.net/SSTM/Time%20for%20a%20power%20assist.png\u0022 alt=\u0022Time for a power assist.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://awesome.redial.net/SSTM/Final%20destination.png\u0022 alt=\u0022Final destination.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Technical Ben","CreatedById":10512,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-12T19:39:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Efoamyesque, I cannot even keep a rocket like that stable, let alone get to the mun. \u0026gt;\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"foamyesque","CreatedById":2982,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-12T19:52:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003Efoamyesque, I cannot even keep a rocket like that stable, let alone get to the mun. \u0026gt;\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWell, I have a joystick, which helps a lot. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Warringer","CreatedById":328,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T00:30:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022foamyesque\u0022 data-cite=\u0022foamyesque\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWell, I have a joystick, which helps a lot. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENot to mention your experience...\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tiberion","CreatedById":8356,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T00:35:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWell, anytime someone mentions overpowered or cheat parts, one only needs to examine how overpowered a stack of normal tanks are.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThat is ridiculous \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Feragorn","CreatedById":7549,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T00:38:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022foamyesque\u0022 data-cite=\u0022foamyesque\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWell, I have a joystick, which helps a lot. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt\\\u0027s doable on WASD as well. \u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"foamyesque","CreatedById":2982,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T01:47:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Feragorn\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Feragorn\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt\\\u0027s doable on WASD as well.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYes, but, having done both, it\\\u0027s MUCH easier with a stick. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"thorfinn","CreatedById":8349,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T01:51:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tiberion\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Tiberion\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWell, anytime someone mentions overpowered or cheat parts, one only needs to examine how overpowered a stack of normal tanks are.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe thing that bugs me about standard parts is how they disfavour staging. Oftentimes, when you try to make a \u0027correct\u0027 rocket you are just causing yourself more trouble; problem is, Kerbin is so small that being able to do SSTO easily IS actually realistic... balancing for the campaign mode will not be an obvious proposition, at all.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EUsing Sundaypunch\\\u0027s parts (plus silisko\\\u0027s lunar lander leg), it\\\u0027s really very simple to go to the Mun in a single stage. The tiny liquid fuel engine is very efficient and a cluster of seven are powerful enough to do the job.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHey, that\\\u0027s the Delta Clipper! \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NovaSilisko","CreatedById":3897,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T05:05:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022thorfinn\u0022 data-cite=\u0022thorfinn\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe thing that bugs me about standard parts is how they disfavour staging. Oftentimes, when you try to make a \u0027correct\u0027 rocket you are just causing yourself more trouble; problem is, Kerbin is so small that being able to do SSTO easily IS actually realistic... balancing for the campaign mode will not be an obvious proposition, at all.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThat\\\u0027s the absolute number one thing I hate about vanilla parts. They DISCOURAGE staging. Engines and decouplers are apparently made of lead...\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Feragorn","CreatedById":7549,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T05:23:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EPlus ASAS and RCS are all wonky, so you get underpowered RCS trying to hold an overpowered ASAS module stable. Which means you flip around and around in space.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RedRockets","CreatedById":10539,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T09:48:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022foamyesque\u0022 data-cite=\u0022foamyesque\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWell, I have a joystick, which helps a lot. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhat kind of Joystick do you use?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInterested in buying one but don\\\u0027t want to waste my cash.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"foamyesque","CreatedById":2982,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T10:18:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ESaitek X52.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SmiteZero","CreatedById":10862,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T12:39:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022foamyesque\u0022 data-cite=\u0022foamyesque\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESaitek X52.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhich is a bit extreme just for KSP, Rockets, FYI before you go looking for one. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"flying_chair","CreatedById":10362,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T13:45:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI fail at taking off on KERBIN! You excpect me to land on the MUN?!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PeriapsisPrograde","CreatedById":33,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T13:53:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NovaSilisko\u0022 data-cite=\u0022NovaSilisko\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003E...decouplers are apparently made of lead...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESee the attached craft. If you adjust the stages so that the booster fires before the decouplers, it won\\\u0027t get off the ground \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_ohmy.png\u0022 alt=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Plymouth","CreatedById":8420,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T16:03:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWARNING!Lots of screenshots.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://s42.radikal.ru/i097/1111/60/5768c083bcbb.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00225768c083bcbb.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://s017.radikal.ru/i434/1111/58/7d75e0b439d5.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00227d75e0b439d5.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://s017.radikal.ru/i417/1111/ce/01238cba8877.jpg\u0022 alt=\u002201238cba8877.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://s59.radikal.ru/i166/1111/50/f4da27180aae.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022f4da27180aae.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://s017.radikal.ru/i415/1111/cc/d1872ec641e6.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022d1872ec641e6.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://s017.radikal.ru/i412/1111/d5/68b454290d03.jpg\u0022 alt=\u002268b454290d03.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://s017.radikal.ru/i444/1111/b0/077130295d1c.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022077130295d1c.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://s017.radikal.ru/i403/1111/da/07ef9811ca84.jpg\u0022 alt=\u002207ef9811ca84.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://s19.radikal.ru/i192/1111/66/3f805982e96c.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00223f805982e96c.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis spaceplane\\\u0027s codename is SpaceBird-X(because of wings)38. It has enough fuel to fly to the mun and back, and even escape kerbin gravitation, but the furhest point this plane can get to is orbit around the sun.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SteevyT","CreatedById":6183,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T16:19:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Plymouth\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Plymouth\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://s017.radikal.ru/i417/1111/ce/01238cba8877.jpg\u0022 alt=\u002201238cba8877.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EShrink that up into the corner and display apoapsis and periapsis values at all time and that would be a perfect minimap view for the flight window!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Plymouth","CreatedById":8420,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T16:22:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWe should post an idea about the mini map to suggestion forum \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"trvtannenberg","CreatedById":8491,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-11-13T16:23:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SteevyT\u0022 data-cite=\u0022SteevyT\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003EShrink that up into the corner and display apoapsis and periapsis values at all time and that would be a perfect minimap view for the flight window!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDefinitely want.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}